latestPosts.caption:
Small 3 months transformation ⬇️

From counting beer bottles to counting calories,
From eating junk to eating clean,
From eating 'for taste' to eating 'for fuel',
From sugary foods to absolutely zero sugar,
From falling down to getting back up,
I just became even more disciplined.

This is just a mini transformation. On to my next transformation & this time I am dead serious about transforming to a better version of myself. I know what I am capable of and time to prove it.

This comeback is personal & an apology to myself. 

Thanks to all who were there in my journey and hoping to stay the same going forward because this time I won't let myself down.

NEW JOURNEY. SAME MINDSET
..
.

latestPosts.caption:
⬇️⬇️

1. SUGAR
Excessive sugar intake can lead to a caloric surplus, promoting fat storage.

Follow @rajatfitzone for more information 🤝

2.Sugary Drinks: (Coke, Sprite, etc)
Empty calories that don't fill you up and leave you crashing later. I didn't even realize how much they were affecting me until I cut them-felt way better and way less bloated instantly.

3.Alcohol
Slows fat loss, adds empty calories, and usually leads to eating junk after. I started slowly and then I cut it completely - and it made a massive difference 

4.Fast Food & Fried Foods:
Loaded with low-quality fats and calories that just leave
you feel heavy. Switched to healthier options.

5. Cereal & Granola bar : 
These seem "healthy"but most are packed with sugar and refined carbs that spike your blood sugar and leave you hungrier an hour later.

PRO TIP : 
Work on your abdominal muscles just like other body muscles. You will thank me later😉
